values: 愤怒；恼怒；激怒；忿怒；愤慨；（对不公正或不道德行为的）义愤

word_mean_info__list.difference: 语气最强，指极端的气愤，甚至达到发疯的程度。
普通用词，通常指因受到侮辱、损害、指责或顶撞等而引起的愤怒。
文学用词，含义与anger相近，但语气强，含欲加惩罚或报复的意味。
侧重突然而猛列发作，难以控制的大怒。
较正式用词，指出于正义或对不公正之事而发出的愤怒。

word_group.brief_definition: 愤怒管理；生气情绪管理；愤怒情绪管理
悲伤和愤怒；悲痛和愤怒；愤怒和悲伤
表示愤怒；显出愤怒的情绪
怨气冲天；越来越不满；愤怒情绪增长
发泄愤怒；释放愤怒情绪

bilingual.source: Feeling the strong emotions of love, anger, fear and grief in the performance, I could easily recognise the theme of Hamlet.
bilingual.target: 感受到表演中强烈的爱、愤怒、恐惧和悲伤的情感，我很容易认出哈姆雷特的主题。
她的眼睛因愤怒而燃烧。
他的愤怒终于爆裂出来。

yingyinNormal.en: Interesting fact: "Irritable" comes from the Latin, "Susceptible to anger."
yingyinNormal.zh: 说一个有趣小知识："易怒"这词来自拉丁语，"容易愤怒"。

yingyinNormal.en: I feel anger for the one who took mother's life. An anger I cannot control.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很恨夺走我母亲生命的人，我控制不了这种愤怒。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't. Something that big? I need the situation, the anger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能，那种大事？我需要环境，那种愤怒。

yingyinNormal.en: Anger is a weed growing in our garden. And what do you do when you find a weed?
yingyinNormal.zh: 愤怒是破坏我们家园的杂草，当发现杂草时你会怎么做？

yingyinNormal.en: Break time's over. Get your work done. Looks like someone has an issue with anger franagement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 休息时间结束了，去完成工作。看来某人的愤怒"朋理"有些问题啊。

yingyinNormal.en: So now, what am I to make of the likes of you? There seems to be a recurring issue here. Anger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么我该怎么解释你这样的存在呢？你身上有一个改不掉的坏毛病，愤怒。

yingyinNormal.en: Today we're gonna be working on managing our anger through movement. The first pose is the dancer pose. Great form, Terence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天我们一起学习一个方法来管理我们的愤怒，用肢体活动，第一个动作，叫做舞者式，做得很好，大红。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Red, given the severity of the crimes, I have no choice but to impose the maximum penalty allowed by the law. Anger management class.
yingyinNormal.zh: 胖红先生，鉴于你的罪行性质恶劣，我只能从重发落，对你判处法律规定范围内最严重的刑罚，接受愤怒管理课程。

yingyinNormal.en: Though you may have the anger now.
That's Anger. He cares very deeply about things being fair.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是"怒怒"，他特别讨厌不公平的事。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't think I have an anger issue. I think you got an anger issue.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我才没有毛病，我看你倒是病得不轻。

yingyinNormal.en: Number three, try to let go of the anger, and learn to love yourself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第三、试着放掉你们的怒气，学会爱护自己。

yingyinNormal.en: I may have some unresolved anger from my childhood. Hey, check this out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可能还在为小时候的事生我爸妈的气，你看。

yingyinNormal.en: What happened? I tried to let go of anger and threw a rock into my foot!
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么回事？我试图释放我的气愤，结果扔石头砸到我的脚了。

yingyinNormal.en: A man with breathtaking anger-management issues, a couple of master assassins, and you, big fella.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个脾气发作就要人命的大块头，还有一对精英杀手，而你呢，倒楣蛋。

yingyinNormal.en: Fair warning, may be working out some anger issues on the racquetball court this morning. Don't ask. Sounds good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说明一下，今早的壁球训练我可能要发泄一下情绪，别问原因。没问题。

yingyinNormal.en: By the end of the evening, all I felt was detached, neutral. No fireworks, no leftover anger no flutters, nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 晚饭快结束的时候，我觉得我像个局外人，旁观者，没有烟火，没有残余的气愤，没有不安，什么都没有。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The threat of nationalisation will return with a vengeance if the justified <highlight>anger</highlight> of passengers is not addressed in short order.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果乘客的合理愤怒不能在短时间内得到解决，国有化的威胁将卷土重来。

examination_example.sentence: Jealousy and <highlight>anger</highlight>, for example, may have evolved to alert us to important inequalities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，嫉妒和愤怒可能已经进化为提醒我们对重要的不平等保持警惕。

examination_example.sentence: Unlike so-called basic emotions such as <highlight>anger</highlight>, guilt emerges a little later.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与愤怒等所谓的基本情绪不同，内疚出现的时间要晚一些。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 意为“愤慨”，常指因某事卑鄙可耻、不公平而感到极其愤怒。
意为“狂怒狂暴”，强调某种难以压制或勉强压制住的愤怒心情。
意为“狂怒”，表示已愤怒到失去自我控制的地步，有强烈的情感外露。

examination_example.sentence: One of the first steps in dealing with emotions such as <highlight>anger</highlight> or fear is to acknowledge them as normal and human.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 处理愤怒或恐惧等情绪的第一步是承认它们是正常的、有人情味的。

examination_example.sentence: Unburdening yourself of frustration and perhaps even <highlight>anger</highlight> to someone who isn't a friend or close colleague can be wonderfully freeing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 向不是朋友或亲密同事的人倾诉自己的沮丧甚至愤怒，这是一种很棒的释放。

examination_example.sentence: You can engage in an argument respectfully without stirring up (激起) <highlight>anger</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你可以有礼貌地进行争论，不用挑起事端激起愤怒。

examination_example.sentence: Readers also tended to share articles that inspired negative feelings like <highlight>anger</highlight> or anxiety, but not articles that left them merely sad.
